                <h2>Festivals of Light</h2>
                <block class="mm_customText">
                    <block class="mm_customImage">
                        <image src="p068a.png" title=""/>
                    </block>
                    <p>Many holidays are celebrated with lights. In Thailand, there’s a Festival of Light called Loi Krathong. People make small boats from banana leaves. They put candles, flowers, and money in them. They light the candles and float the boats on the river by moonlight. People believe that the boats take away bad luck. Many cities around the world like Singapore and Sydney have light festivals. People use lights to make beautiful pictures on buildings or bridges. You can see the lights reflected in the water, too! These festivals often happen in winter because it’s nice to make the dark a little brighter.</p>
                </block>
